```

### Local Development
```bash
pip install -e .
```


## ðŸ“˜ Usage
### ðŸ”¹Load a Dataset
```bash
from tools_managed_file.exporter import load_dataset

df = load_dataset("data.csv")
print(df)

```


### ðŸ”¹Export a Dataset to CSV
```bash
from tools_managed_file.exporter import export_dataset
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame([
    {"name": "Adam", "age": 20},
    {"name": "Sarah", "age": 22}
])

output = export_dataset(df, "outputs", "student-data")
print("Exported to:", output)

```

Generates:
```bash
outputs/student-data.csv
```

### ðŸ”¹Duplicate a File
```bash
duplicate-file input.csv --count 5
```

Creates:
```bash
input_copy_1.csv
input_copy_2.csv
input_copy_3.csv
input_copy_4.csv
input_copy_5.csv
```

## ðŸ”§ CLI Commands
### âœ” Exporting
```bash
export-file input.xlsx --output out --name cleaned
```

### âœ” Exporting
```bash
duplicate-file report.pdf --count 3
```

